I personally am not a big fan of WAGOS. I prefer Anderson Power Poles because  
(a) they are a one-and-done solution—once crimped, they can be slid onto wires without frequently removing them from connectors, which can become cumbersome with Spark MAX wires;  
(b) they can be ziptied together to prevent sliding;  
(c) they can be stacked to form a large block that is easy to plug or unplug.  

However, if you choose to use WAGOs, I recommend this video from Team 11. Additionally, having flexible, high-quality wire, like what we found from PowerWerx, makes handling much easier. This thread also offers valuable insights.
